      "message": "Alarm states are dynamic — they change whenever a reading crosses a threshold. This means the first response is correct, but all subsequent responses for the same sensor return stale data.\n\nEX:\n\n1. Sensor 0x10 reads 28°C, upper warning threshold is 45°C → alarm is `false`. Cached.\n2. Threshold is later changed to 20°C → 28°C now exceeds it → alarm should be `true`.\n3. Next call returns cached `false` — incorrect.\n\nBetter If may fetch fresh data",
